article.headline: Kent State 77, Montana State 61
article.story:
KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Senior Lindsay Shearer scored 28 points and
grabbed seven rebounds to lead Kent State past Montana State 77-61
on Saturday.

Montana State (0-5) freshman Jenny Heringer had 15 points to
lead three Bobcat players in double figures, but it wasn't enough.
Kent State (4-1) shot 40 percent from the field and outrebounded
MSU 41-36.

The Golden Flashes led 33-23 at the half and built their lead to
12 points before the Bobcats rallied to cut the margin to 44-40
with 13 minutes remaining. Kent State answered with its own 16-2
run to put the game away for good.

Also in double digits for Montana State were Alyssa Nelson with
11 points and Scotta Morton with 10. Nelson had a team-high five
assists, while sophomore Amanda DeHaan tallied eight points and
seven rebounds.

The Bobcats shot 39 percent from the field and converted
15-of-17 free throws, but had 28 turnovers.

The team hosts Long Beach State on Thursday night in Worthington
Arena.
